Here is some sample pseudocode for a motion forecasting algorithm used in AVs:
```
// Define the input data
input_data = [
  sensor_data (camera, lidar, radar, etc.)
  object_properties (position, velocity, acceleration)
]

// Define the model architecture
model = [
  convolutional_neural_network (CNN)
  recurrent_neural_network (RNN)
  fully_connected_neural_network (FCN)
]

// Train the model
model.train(input_data)

// Use the model to make predictions
predictions = model.predict(sensor_data)

// Filter the predictions based on confidence
filtered_predictions = filter(predictions, confidence > 0.5)

// Use the filtered predictions to update the vehicle's trajectory
vehicle_trajectory = update_trajectory(filtered_predictions)
```
And here is some sample pseudocode for an intent prediction algorithm used in AVs:
```
// Define the input data
input_data = [
  sensor_data (camera, lidar, radar, etc.)
  object_properties (position, velocity, acceleration)
  historical_data (past behavior of objects in the environment)
]

// Define the model architecture
model = [
  convolutional_neural_network (CNN)
  recurrent_neural_network (RNN)
  fully_connected_neural_network (FCN)
]

// Train the model
model.train(input_data)

// Use the model to make predictions
predictions = model.predict(sensor_data)

// Filter the predictions based on confidence
filtered_predictions = filter(predictions, confidence > 0.5)

// Use the filtered predictions to update the vehicle's trajectory
vehicle_trajectory = update_trajectory(filtered_predictions)

// Use the vehicle's trajectory to make decisions about acceleration, braking, and steering
vehicle_control = make_decisions(vehicle_trajectory)
```
Note that this is highly simplified pseudocode and actual implementations would be much more complex and sophisticated.
